{"nodes":[{"pos":[11,70],"content":"Game technologies for Universal Windows Platform (UWP) apps","needQuote":true,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Game technologies for Universal Windows Platform (UWP) apps","pos":[0,59]}]},{"pos":[84,199],"content":"In this guide, you'll learn about the technologies available for developing Universal Windows Platform (UWP) games.","needQuote":true,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"In this guide, you'll learn about the technologies available for developing Universal Windows Platform (UWP) games.","pos":[0,115]}]},{"content":"Game technologies for Universal Windows Platform (UWP) apps","pos":[256,315]},{"content":"\\[ Updated for UWP apps on Windows 10.","pos":[318,356]},{"content":"For Windows 8.x articles, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>archive<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=619132)</ept> \\]","pos":[357,452],"source":" For Windows 8.x articles, see the [archive](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=619132) \\]"},{"content":"In this guide, you'll learn about the technologies available for developing Universal Windows Platform (UWP) games.","pos":[454,569]},{"content":"Benefits of Windows 10 for game development","pos":[575,618]},{"content":"With the introduction of UWP in Windows 10, your Windows 10 titles will be able to span all of the Microsoft platforms.","pos":[621,740]},{"content":"With free migration from previous versions of Windows, there is a steadily increasing number of Windows 10 clients.","pos":[741,856]},{"content":"The combination of these two things means that your Windows 10 titles will be able to reach a huge number of customers through the Windows Store.","pos":[857,1002]},{"content":"In addition, Windows 10 offers many new features that are particularly beneficial to games:","pos":[1004,1095]},{"content":"Reduced memory paging and reduced overall memory system size","pos":[1101,1161]},{"content":"Improved graphics memory management actively allocates and protects more memory for the foreground game","pos":[1166,1269]},{"content":"UWP Games with C++ and DirectX","pos":[1274,1304]},{"content":"Real-time games requiring high performance should make use of the DirectX APIs.","pos":[1307,1386]},{"content":"DirectX is a collection of native APIs for creating games and multimedia applications that require high performance, such as 3D games.","pos":[1387,1521]},{"content":"Because the DirectX APIs are native, C++ is the only language supported for use with DirectX.","pos":[1522,1615]},{"content":"Development Environment","pos":[1620,1643]},{"content":"To create games for UWP, you'll need to set up your development environment by installing a copy of Visual Studio 2015.","pos":[1646,1765]},{"content":"Visual Studio 2015 allows you to create UWP apps and provides tools for game development:","pos":[1766,1855]},{"content":"Visual Studio tools for DX game programming - Visual Studio provides tools for creating, editing, previewing, and exporting image, model, and shader resources.","pos":[1861,2020]},{"content":"There are also tools that you can use to convert resources at build time and debug DirectX graphics code.","pos":[2021,2126]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Use Visual Studio tools for game programming<ept id=\"p1\">](set-up-visual-studio-for-game-development.md)</ept>.","pos":[2127,2246],"source":" For more information, see [Use Visual Studio tools for game programming](set-up-visual-studio-for-game-development.md)."},{"content":"Visual Studio graphics diagnostics features - Graphics diagnostic tools are now available from within Windows as an optional feature.","pos":[2251,2384]},{"content":"The diagnostic tools allow you to do graphics debugging, graphics frame analysis, and monitor GPU usage in real time.","pos":[2385,2502]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Use the DirectX runtime and Visual Studio graphics diagnostic features<ept id=\"p1\">](use-the-directx-runtime-and-visual-studio-graphics-diagnostic-features.md)</ept>.","pos":[2503,2677],"source":" For more information, see [Use the DirectX runtime and Visual Studio graphics diagnostic features](use-the-directx-runtime-and-visual-studio-graphics-diagnostic-features.md)."},{"content":"For more information, see Prepare your Universal Windows Platform and DirectX game programming environment.","pos":[2679,2786]},{"content":"Getting Started with DirectX Game Project Templates","pos":[2791,2842]},{"content":"After setting up you development environment, you can use one of the DirectX related project templates to create your UWP DirectX game.","pos":[2845,2980]},{"content":"Visual Studio 2015 has three templates available for creating new UWP DirectX projects, <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>DirectX 11 App (Universal Windows)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>DirectX 12 App (Universal Windows)<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>DirectX 11 and XAML App (Universal Windows)<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>.","pos":[2981,3201],"source":" Visual Studio 2015 has three templates available for creating new UWP DirectX projects, **DirectX 11 App (Universal Windows)**, **DirectX 12 App (Universal Windows)**, and **DirectX 11 and XAML App (Universal Windows)**."},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a Universal Windows Platform and DirectX game project from a template<ept id=\"p1\">](user-interface.md)</ept>.","pos":[3202,3326],"source":" For more information, see [Create a Universal Windows Platform and DirectX game project from a template](user-interface.md)."},{"content":"Windows 10 APIs","pos":[3331,3346]},{"content":"Windows 10 provides a an extensive collection of APIs that are useful for game development.","pos":[3349,3440]},{"content":"There are APIs for almost all aspects of games including, 3D Graphics, 2D Graphics, Audio, Input, Text Resources, User Interface, and networking.","pos":[3441,3586]},{"content":"There are many APIs related to game development, but not all games need to use all of the APIs.","pos":[3588,3683]},{"content":"For example, some games will only use 3D graphics and only make use of Direct3D, some games may only use 2D graphics and only make use of Direct2D, and still other games may make use of both.","pos":[3684,3875]},{"content":"The following diagram shows the game development related APIs grouped by functionality type.","pos":[3876,3968]},{"content":"game platform technologies","pos":[3972,3998]},{"content":"3D Graphics - Windows 10 supports two 3D graphics API sets, Direct3D 11, and <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Direct3D 12<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/dn899121)</ept>.","pos":[4042,4194],"source":"3D Graphics - Windows 10 supports two 3D graphics API sets, Direct3D 11, and [Direct3D 12](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/dn899121)."},{"content":"Both of these APIs provide the capability to create 3D and 2D graphics.","pos":[4195,4266]},{"content":"Direct3D 11 and Direct3D 12 are not used together, but either can be used with any of the APIs in the 2D Graphics and UI group.","pos":[4267,4394]},{"content":"For more information about using the graphics APIs in your game, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Basic 3D graphics for DirectX games<ept id=\"p1\">](an-introduction-to-3d-graphics-with-directx.md)</ept>.","pos":[4395,4550],"source":" For more information about using the graphics APIs in your game, see [Basic 3D graphics for DirectX games](an-introduction-to-3d-graphics-with-directx.md)."},{"pos":[4556,6235],"content":"<table>\n<colgroup>\n<col width=\"50%\" />\n<col width=\"50%\" />\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"header\">\n<th align=\"left\">API</th>\n<th align=\"left\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td align=\"left\">Direct3D 12</td>\n<td align=\"left\"><p>Direct3D 12 introduces the next version of Direct3D, the 3D graphics API at the heart of DirectX. This version of Direct3D is designed to be faster and more efficient than previous versions of Direct3D. The tradeoff for Direct3D 12's increased speed is that it is lower level and requires you to manage your graphics resources yourself and have more extensive graphics programming experience to realize the increased speed.</p>\n<p><strong>When to use</strong></p>\n<p>Use Direct3D 12 when you need to maximize your game's performance and your game is CPU bound.</p>\n<p><strong>For more information</strong></p>\n<p>See the [Direct3d 12](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/dn899121) documentation.</p></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td align=\"left\">Direct3D 11</td>\n<td align=\"left\"><p>Direct3D 11 is the previous version of Direct3D and allows you to create 3D graphics using a higher level of hardware abstraction than D3D 12.</p>\n<p><strong>When to use</strong></p>\n<p>Use Direct3D 11 if you have existing Direct3D 11 code, your game is not CPU bound, or you want the benefit of having resources managed for you.</p>\n<p><strong>For more information</strong></p>\n<p>See the [Direct3D 11](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/ff476080) documentation.</p></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","leadings":["","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    "],"nodes":[{"content":"API","pos":[116,119]},{"content":"Description","pos":[142,153]},{"content":"Direct3D 12","pos":[216,227]},{"content":"Direct3D 12 introduces the next version of Direct3D, the 3D graphics API at the heart of DirectX. This version of Direct3D is designed to be faster and more efficient than previous versions of Direct3D. The tradeoff for Direct3D 12's increased speed is that it is lower level and requires you to manage your graphics resources yourself and have more extensive graphics programming experience to realize the increased speed.","pos":[253,676],"nodes":[{"content":"D