ming.Input</strong>](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/dn707817) documentation."},{"content":"Windows.UI.Core.CoreWindow","pos":[1898,1924]},{"content":"The Windows.UI.Core.CoreWindow class provides events for tracking pointer presses and movement, and key down and key up events.","pos":[1950,2077]},{"content":"When to use","pos":[2093,2104]},{"content":"Use Windows.UI.Core.CoreWindows events when you need to track the mouse or key presses in your game.","pos":[2121,2221]},{"content":"For more information","pos":[2237,2257]},{"content":"See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Move-look controls for games<ept id=\"p1\">](tutorial--adding-move-look-controls-to-your-directx-game.md)</ept> for more information about using the mouse or keyboard in your game.","pos":[2274,2438],"source":"See [Move-look controls for games](tutorial--adding-move-look-controls-to-your-directx-game.md) for more information about using the mouse or keyboard in your game."}]},{"content":"Math - APIs concerning simplifying commonly used mathematical operations.","pos":[13778,13851]},{"pos":[13857,14636],"content":"<table>\n<colgroup>\n<col width=\"50%\" />\n<col width=\"50%\" />\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"header\">\n<th align=\"left\">API</th>\n<th align=\"left\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td align=\"left\">DirectXMath</td>\n<td align=\"left\"><p>The DirectXMath API provides SIMD-friendly C++ types and functions for common linear algebra and graphics math operations common to games.</p>\n<p><strong>When to use</strong></p>\n<p>Use of DirectXMath is optional and simplifies common mathematical operations.</p>\n<p><strong>For more information</strong></p>\n<p>See the [DirectXMath](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/hh437833) documentation.</p></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","leadings":["","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    ","    "],"